    {
      "name": "OUTFILE",
      "description": "File to receive output",
      "help": "File to receive output (OUTFILE)\n\nSpecifies the database file to which the output of the command is directed. If the file does not exist, this command creates a database file in the specified library. If the file is created, the public authority for the file is the same as the create authority specified for the library in which the file is created. Use the Display Library Description (DSPLIBD) command to show the library's create authority.\n\nQualifier 1: File to receive output\n\nQualifier 2: Library\n\nNote: If a new file is created, the system uses as a model one of the following output files in QSYS with one of the following format names, depending on the values specified on the Type of information prompt (TYPE parameter) and the File attributes prompt (FILATR parameter). For more information about the OUTFILE format, refer to Database category in the IBM i Information Center at http://www.ibm.com/systems/i/infocenter/.\n\nNote: You must specify the FILEATR parameter only when TYPE(*ATR) is used. The default of FILEATR(*ALL) is valid on any of the other TYPE values as long as you are requesting file types that match the appropriate request.",
      "inputType": "group",
      "required": false,
      "groupKind": "qualified",
      "children": [
        {
          "name": "OUTFILE_LIB",
          "description": "Library",
          "help": "指定できる特殊値: *LIBL, *CURLIB",
          "inputType": "text",
          "required": false,
          "defaultValue": "*LIBL",
          "attributes": {
            "characterSet": "upper",
            "maxLength": 10
          },
          "placeholder": "*LIBL"
